The paper focuses on image decomposition and fusion, which are core topics in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method is based on latent low-rank representation, which is a popular technique in matrix completion and multi-modal learning (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the use of nuclear-norm based fusion strategy, which is a common optimization technique in information theory (cs.IT). The proposed algorithm involves machine learning techniques such as feature extraction and fusion, which are also relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
